routeFacts.name: Great Western Express
routeFacts.operators: Great Western Railway, DB Cargo UK
routeFacts.description: The Great Western Express route is the first DLC for Train Sim World. The route covers the Great Western Main Line between London Paddington and Reading and includes the GWR Classes 43 and 166 as well as the DB Cargo Class 66. This route is set between 2015 and 2016, at a time when the line was undergoing extensive upgrade works in anticipation of new units, as well as the completion of Crossrail.
routeInfo: The Great Western Express route covers the Great Western Main Line from London Paddington station to Reading, a distance of 36 miles. It is set in 2015, when the survey for the route was undertaken, prior to the electrification of the Great Western Main Line beyond Maidenhead. Both InterCity and commuter trains are operated by Great Western Railway along the route with freight services being operated by DB Cargo UK, formerly known as DB Schenker or EWS. Unloading facilities for HKA Hoppers are located at Hayes & Harlington as well as at Acton.
